Run the Project Locally (via Docker Compose)

You can run the entire project locally using Docker Compose. This is useful for testing and understanding the microservices architecture before deploying to the cloud.

Prerequisites:
- Docker & Docker Compose installed
- Git installed (git --version)
- Optional: AWS EC2 instance if running on cloud

Steps:
1. Clone the Repository
   git clone <your_project_url>
   cd ultimate-devops-project-demo

2. Run with Docker Compose
   docker-compose up -d
   (Use docker-compose up to see logs)

3. Verify Containers Are Running
   docker ps

Access the Application:
- Local: http://localhost
- EC2:
  - Update security group to allow HTTP (port 80)
  - Get public IP: curl ifconfig.me
  - Access: http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>

Optional Cleanup:
docker system prune -a --volumes -f

Disk Space Troubleshooting on EC2:
- Check disk usage: df -h
- Resize EBS volume in AWS Console
- SSH and run:
  sudo growpart /dev/xvda 1
  sudo resize2fs /dev/xvda1  # for ext4
